  "text": "## TiDB Privilege and RBAC Enforcement Audit\n\n### Privilege Management Architecture\n\nThe privilege and RBAC enforcement system in TiDB is a multi-layered architecture with privilege checking occurring at both planning and execution stages:\n\n### 1. Core Manager Interface (pkg/privilege/privilege.go)\n\n**Manager Interface** (lines 44-123):\n- Central abstraction for privilege operations\n- Key methods:\n  - `RequestVerification(activeRole, db, table, column, priv)`: Checks user privilege at global, database, table, or column level\n  - `RequestDynamicVerification(activeRoles, privName, grantable)`: Checks dynamic privileges (BACKUP_ADMIN, RESTORE_ADMIN, SYSTEM_USER, etc.)\n  - `RequestVerificationWithUser()`: Verifies specific user privilege\n  - `ConnectionVerification()`: Verifies privilege during connection establishment\n  - `ActiveRoles()`, `GetAllRoles()`, `GetDefaultRoles()`: Role management\n  - `FindEdge()`: Checks role graph edges\n\n**Context Binding Functions**:\n- `BindPrivilegeManager()`: Attaches Manager to session context (lines 127-129)\n- `GetPrivilegeManager()`: Retrieves Manager from context (lines 137-143)\n\n### 2. MySQLPrivilege Cache (pkg/privilege/privileges/cache.go)\n\n**MySQLPrivilege struct** (lines 286-300):\nThe in-memory privilege cache implementing the core privilege lookup logic:\n- Embedded `immutable` struct containing: user records, db records, tables_priv records, columns_priv records, default_roles, global_priv, dynamic privileges, and role graph\n- Extended struct for accelerated lookups via maps\n\n**Role Graph Resolution** (lines 314-348):\n- `FindAllRole()` (lines 314-337): Breadth-first search (BFS) algorithm to traverse role hierarchy and find all effective roles for a user\n  - Uses queue-based iteration over roleGraph to discover transitive role memberships\n  - Maintains visited set to prevent cycles\n  - Critical for determining which privileges a user has through role inheritance\n\n- `FindRole()` (lines 339-348): Detects direct edges between users and roles\n\n- `roleGraphEdgesTable` (lines 248-264): Represents relationships between users/roles\n  - `Find(user, host)`: Checks if a specific role is in the graph\n\n- `LoadRoleGraph()` (lines 540-548): Loads mysql.role_edges table from database into memory cache\n  - Initializes the roleGraph map structure\n  - Uses `decodeRoleEdgesTable()` to parse SQL results\n\n**RequestVerification Implementation** (lines 1332-1387):\nCore privilege checking logic with four-level scope checking:\n1. **Global level**: Checks user privileges (lines 1342-1350)\n2. **Database level**: Checks DB-scoped privileges (lines 1352-1360)\n3. **Table level**: Checks table and column privileges (lines 1362-1373)\n4. **Column level**: Checks column-specific privileges (lines 1375-1384)\n\nFor each scope, the implementation:\n- Iterates through all effective roles via `FindAllUserEffectiveRoles()`\n- Accumulates privileges with bitwise OR\n- Returns true if the required privilege is present at any scope level\n\n**Helper Methods**:\n- `FindAllUserEffectiveRoles()` (lines 302-312): Filters active roles to only those actually granted to the user\n- `LoadUserTable()`, `LoadDBTable()`, `LoadTablesPrivTable()`, `LoadColumnsPrivTable()`: Load privilege tables\n\n### 3. UserPrivileges Wrapper (pkg/privilege/privileges/privileges.go)\n\n**UserPrivileges struct** (lines 74-85):\nImplements `privilege.Manager` interface, serving as a wrapper around MySQLPrivilege:\n- Stores user identity (username, hostname)\n- Maintains reference to MySQLPrivilege Handle (underlying cache)\n- Integrates extension system hooks for auth plugins\n\n**Key Methods**:\n- `RequestVerification()` (lines 141-150): Delegates to MySQLPrivilege.RequestVerification() with user identity\n- `RequestDynamicVerification()` (lines 125-139): Handles dynamic privilege checks with fallback to SUPER privilege\n- `NewUserPrivileges()` (lines 87-94): Factory for creating UserPrivileges instances\n\n**Dynamic Privileges** (lines 53-70):\nRegistered dynamic privileges include:\n- BACKUP_ADMIN, RESTORE_ADMIN, SYSTEM_USER, SYSTEM_VARIABLES_ADMIN\n- ROLE_ADMIN, CONNECTION_ADMIN, PLACEMENT_ADMIN\n- RESTRICTED_* variants (TABLES_ADMIN, VARIABLES_ADMIN, etc.)\n- RESOURCE_GROUP_ADMIN, RESOURCE_GROUP_USER\n\n### 4. SQL Statement Privilege Mapping (pkg/planner/core/)\n\n**visitInfo struct** (planbuilder.go, lines 81-92):\nRepresents a privilege requirement for SQL statement execution:\n```go\ntype visitInfo struct {\n    privilege       mysql.PrivilegeType  // Static privilege required\n    db              string               // Database scope\n    table           string               // Table scope\n    column          string               // Column scope\n    dynamicPrivs    []string             // Dynamic privileges (alternatives)\n    dynamicWithGrant bool                // Whether GRANT option required\n}\n```\n\n**Statement-to-Privilege Mappings** (logical_plan_builder.go):\n\nDifferent SQL statements add visitInfo entries during planning:\n- **SELECT statements**: Adds SelectPriv (line 3471)\n- **INSERT statements** (buildInsert, line 4396): Adds InsertPriv; adds DeletePriv if ON DUPLICATE KEY REPLACE\n- **UPDATE statements**: Adds UpdatePriv and SelectPriv\n- **DELETE statements**: Adds DeletePriv and SelectPriv\n- **CREATE TABLE**: Adds CreatePriv (special handling for temporary tables with CreateTMPTablePriv)\n- **ALTER TABLE**: Adds AlterPriv and SelectPriv\n- **CREATE/DROP/ALTER DATABASE**: Adds CreatePriv/DropPriv\n- **GRANT/REVOKE**: Adds GrantPriv or dynamic privilege checks\n- **CREATE/DROP USER**: Adds CreateUserPriv or CreateRolePriv\n- **ADMIN statements**: Various ADMIN privileges based on operation type\n\n**Helper Functions**:\n- `appendVisitInfo()` (logical_plan_builder.go, lines 7105-7109): Appends static privilege requirement\n- `appendDynamicVisitInfo()` (logical_plan_builder.go, lines 7096-7100): Appends dynamic privilege requirement\n- `appendVisitInfoIsRestrictedUser()` (planbuilder.go, lines 3737-3750): Adds RESTRICTED_USER_ADMIN check when SEM is enabled\n\n### 5. Privilege Checking Pipeline (pkg/planner/core/optimizer.go)\n\n**CheckPrivilege()** (lines 125-150):\nValidates accumulated visitInfo entries:\n1. Iterates through all visitInfo entries collected during planning\n2. For each entry:\n   - If dynamic privilege (mysql.ExtendedPriv):\n     - Calls `RequestDynamicVerification()` for each privilege name\n     - Requires at least one privilege match (OR logic)\n   - If static privilege:\n     - Calls `RequestVerification()` with db/table/column scope\n     - Requires exact privilege match\n3. Returns error if any privilege check fails\n\n**VisitInfo4PrivCheck()** (lines 152-207):\nPost-processing of visitInfo for temporary table handling:\n- For CREATE TEMPORARY TABLE: Changes CreatePriv to CreateTMPTablePriv at database scope\n- For other operations on local temporary tables: Filters out unnecessary privilege checks\n- Ensures compliance with MySQL temporary table privilege semantics\n\n### 6. Planning-Time Privilege Checking (pkg/planner/optimize.go)\n\nPrivilege checking integration point during statement optimization:\n- **HandleOptimize()** (lines 495-510): After logical plan building, collects visitInfo\n- Calls `core.VisitInfo4PrivCheck()` to adjust for temporary tables\n- Invokes `core.CheckPrivilege()` to validate all collected requirements\n- Blocks execution if privileges insufficient\n\n### 7. Authentication Connection (pkg/privilege/conn/conn.go)\n\n**AuthConn interface** (lines 19-30):\nEnables auth plugins to interact with client during authentication:\n- `WriteAuthMoreData()`: Send authentication challenge data\n- `ReadPacket()`: Receive authentication response from client\n- `Flush()`: Transmit buffered data to client\n\nSupports pluggable authentication mechanisms (PAM, LDAP, JWT, etc.)\n\n### 8. Privilege Check Flow Summary\n\nEnd-to-end flow:\n```\nSQL Statement\n    ↓\nLogical Plan Builder (logical_plan_builder.go)\n  - Collects visitInfo for each table/operation\n  - appendVisitInfo() for static privileges\n  - appendDynamicVisitInfo() for dynamic privileges\n    ↓\nOptimizer (optimizer.go)\n  - VisitInfo4PrivCheck() adjusts for temp tables\n  - CheckPrivilege() validates all visitInfo\n    ↓\nCheckPrivilege() (optimizer.go, line 126-150)\n  - For each visitInfo:\n    - Dynamic: RequestDynamicVerification()\n    - Static: RequestVerification()\n    ↓\nUserPrivileges.RequestVerification() (privileges.go, line 142)\n  - Delegates to MySQLPrivilege via Handle.Get()\n    ↓\nMySQLPrivilege.RequestVerification() (cache.go, line 1332)\n  - Calls FindAllUserEffectiveRoles()\n  - Checks global/db/table/column privilege levels\n  - Iterates through role graph for inherited privileges\n    ↓\nFindAllRole() (cache.go, line 314) - BFS Role Resolution\n  - Traverses roleGraph via breadth-first search\n  - Returns all effective roles including inherited ones\n```\n\n### 9. Role Inheritance and Dynamic Privilege Support\n\n**Role Graph Handling**:\n- `roleGraph` map keyed by \"user@host\" \n- Each entry contains map of granted roles\n- Supports recursive role inheritance via BFS traversal\n- Critical for supporting ROLE_ADMIN operations and role-based privilege granularity\n\n**Dynamic Privilege Fallback**:\n- SUPER privilege grants all dynamic privileges (except when SEM enabled)\n- Extension plugins can provide additional authorization logic\n- Support for explicit dynamic privilege grants without SUPER\n\n### Key Files in Privilege Check Flow:\n\n1. **pkg/privilege/privilege.go**: Manager interface definition and context binding\n2. **pkg/privilege/privileges/cache.go**: In-memory privilege cache with role graph resolution\n3. **pkg/privilege/privileges/privileges.go**: UserPrivileges wrapper for current session\n4. **pkg/planner/core/planbuilder.go**: visitInfo struct and plan builder initialization\n5. **pkg/planner/core/logical_plan_builder.go**: Statement-specific visitInfo population\n6. **pkg/planner/core/optimizer.go**: Central privilege checking and temporary table handling\n7. **pkg/planner/optimize.go**: Planning pipeline integration point\n8. **pkg/planner/core/plan_cache.go**: Privilege re-verification for cached plans\n9. **pkg/privilege/conn/conn.go**: Authentication connection interface for plugins\n\nThis architecture ensures comprehensive RBAC enforcement where every SQL statement is validated against the user's direct privileges and role-inherited privileges before execution.\n"
